rong.<br /><br />That commit doesn't invert a cleared page table entry, because that<br />commit still required _PAGE_PROTNONE being set for a pte to be<br />inverted.<br /><br />I'm assuming the real culprit is commit f22cc87f6c1f<br />("x86/speculation/l1tf: Invert all not present mappings") which made<br />it look at _just_ the present bit.<br /><br />And yeah, that was wrong.<br /><br />So I really think a much better patch would be the appended one-liner.<br /><br />Note - it's whitespace-damaged by cut-and-paste, but it should be<br />obvious enough to apply by hand.<br /><br />Can you test this one instead?<br /><br />             Linus<br />---<br /><br /> arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable-invert.h | 2 +-<br /> 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)<br /><br />diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable-invert.h<br />b/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable-invert.h<br />index 44b1203ece12..821438e91b77 100644<br />--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable-invert.h<br />+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable-invert.h<br />&#64;&#64; -6,7 +6,7 &#64;&#64;<br /><br /> static inline bool __pte_needs_invert(u64 val)<br /> {<br />-       return !(val &amp; _PAGE_PRESENT);<br />+       return val &amp;&amp; !(val &amp; _PAGE_PRESENT);<br /> }<br /><br /> /* Get a mask to xor with the page table entry to get the correct pfn. */<br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
